<P class=3Dshort-description>Class upload</P>
<P class=3Ddescription>
<P><STRONG>What does it do?</STRONG></P>
<P>It manages file uploads for you. In short, it manages the uploaded =
file, and=20
allows you to do whatever you want with the file, especially if it is an =
image,=20
and as many times as you want.</P>
<P>It is the ideal class to quickly integrate file upload in your site. =
If the=20
file is an image, you can convert, resize, crop it in many ways. You can =
also=20
apply filters, add borders, text, watermarks, etc... That's all you need =
for a=20
gallery script for instance. Supported formats are PNG, JPG, GIF and =
BMP.</P>
<P>You can also use the class to work on local files, which is =
especially useful=20
to use the image manipulation features. The class also supports Flash=20
uploaders.</P>
<P>The class works with PHP 4 and 5, and its error messages can be =
localized at=20
will.</P>
<P><STRONG>How does it work?</STRONG></P>
<P>You instanciate the class with the $_FILES['my_field'] array where =
my_field=20
is the field name from your upload form. The class will check if the =
original=20
file has been uploaded to its temporary location (alternatively, you can =

instanciate the class with a local filename).</P>
<P>You can then set a number of processing variables to act on the file. =
For=20
instance, you can rename the file, and if it is an image, convert and =
resize it=20
in many ways. You can also set what will the class do if the file =
already=20
exists.</P>
<P>Then you call the function <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
to actually perform the actions according to the processing parameters =
you set=20
above. It will create new instances of the original file, so the =
original file=20
remains the same between each process. The file will be manipulated, and =
copied=20
to the given location. The processing variables will be reset once it is =

done.</P>
<P>You can repeat setting up a new set of processing variables, and =
calling <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
again as many times as you want. When you have finished, you can call <A =

href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodclean">c=
lean</A>=20
to delete the original uploaded file.</P>
<P>If you don't set any processing parameters and call <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
just after instanciating the class. The uploaded file will be simply =
copied to=20
the given location without any alteration or checks.</P>
<P>Don't forget to add <EM>enctype=3D"multipart/form-data"</EM> in your =
form tag=20
&lt;form&gt; if you want your form to upload the file.</P>
<P><STRONG>How to use it?</STRONG><BR>Create a simple HTML file, with a =
form=20
such as: <PRE> &lt;form enctype=3D"multipart/form-data" method=3D"post" =
action=3D"upload.php"&gt;
   &lt;input type=3D"file" size=3D"32" name=3D"image_field" =
value=3D""&gt;
   &lt;input type=3D"submit" name=3D"Submit" value=3D"upload"&gt;
 &lt;/form&gt;</PRE>Create a file called upload.php: <PRE>  $handle =3D =
new upload($_FILES['image_field']);
  if ($handle-&gt;uploaded) {
      $handle-&gt;file_new_name_body   =3D 'image_resized';
      $handle-&gt;image_resize         =3D true;
      $handle-&gt;image_x              =3D 100;
      $handle-&gt;image_ratio_y        =3D true;
      $handle-&gt;process('/home/user/files/');
      if ($handle-&gt;processed) {
          echo 'image resized';
          $handle-&gt;clean();
      } else {
          echo 'error : ' . $handle-&gt;error;
      }
  }</PRE>
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>How to process local files?</STRONG><BR>Use the class as =
following,=20
the rest being the same as above: <PRE>  $handle =3D new =
upload('/home/user/myfile.jpg');</PRE>
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>How to set the language?</STRONG><BR>Instantiate the class =
with a=20
second argument being the language code: <PRE>  $handle =3D new =
upload($_FILES['image_field'], 'fr_FR');
  $handle =3D new upload('/home/user/myfile.jpg', 'fr_FR');</PRE>
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>How to output the resulting file or picture directly to the=20
browser?</STRONG><BR>Simply call <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>()=20
without an argument (or with null as first argument): <PRE>  $handle =3D =
new upload($_FILES['image_field']);
  header('Content-type: ' . $handle-&gt;file_src_mime);
  echo $handle-&gt;Process();
  die();</PRE>Or if you want to force the download of the file: <PRE>  =
$handle =3D new upload($_FILES['image_field']);
  header('Content-type: ' . $handle-&gt;file_src_mime);
  header("Content-Disposition: attachment; =
filename=3D".rawurlencode($handle-&gt;file_src_name).";");
  echo $handle-&gt;Process();
  die();</PRE>
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>Processing parameters</STRONG> (reset after each process)=20
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>file_new_name_body</STRONG> replaces the name body =
(default:=20
  '')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_new_name_body =3D 'new name';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_name_body_add</STRONG> appends to the name body =
(default:=20
  '')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_name_body_add =3D '_uploaded';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_name_body_pre</STRONG> prepends to the name body =
(default:=20
  '')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_name_body_pre =3D 'thumb_';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_new_name_ext</STRONG> replaces the file extension =
(default:=20
  '')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_new_name_ext =3D 'txt';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_safe_name</STRONG> formats the filename (spaces =
changed to _)=20
  (default: true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_safe_name =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_overwrite</STRONG> sets behaviour if file already =
exists=20
  (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_overwrite =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_auto_rename</STRONG> automatically renames file if it =
already=20
  exists (default: true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_auto_rename =3D =
true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>auto_create_dir</STRONG> automatically creates destination =

  directory if missing (default: =
true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;auto_create_dir =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>dir_auto_chmod</STRONG> automatically attempts to chmod =
the=20
  destination directory if not writeable (default: =
true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;dir_auto_chmod =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>dir_chmod</STRONG> chmod used when creating directory or =
if=20
  directory not writeable (default: 0777)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;dir_chmod =
=3D 0777;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>file_max_size</STRONG> sets maximum upload size (default:=20
  upload_max_filesize from php.ini)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;file_max_size =
=3D '1024'; // 1KB</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>mime_check</STRONG> sets if the class check the MIME =
against the=20
  <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$allowed">a=
llowed</A>=20
  list (default: true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;mime_check =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>no_script</STRONG> sets if the class turns scripts into =
text files=20
  (default: true)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;no_script =3D false;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>allowed</STRONG> array of allowed mime-types. wildcard =
accepted,=20
  as in image/* (default: check Init)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;allowed =3D =
array('application/pdf','application/msword', 'image/*');</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>forbidden</STRONG> array of forbidden mime-types. wildcard =

  accepted, as in image/* (default: check =
Init)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;forbidden =3D =
array('application/*');</PRE></LI></UL>
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_convert</STRONG> if set, image will be converted =
(possible=20
  values : ''|'png'|'jpeg'|'gif'|'bmp'; default: =
'')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_convert =3D 'jpg';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_background_color</STRONG> if set, will forcibly fill =

  transparent areas with the color, in hexadecimal (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_background_color =3D '#FF00FF';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_default_color</STRONG> fallback color background =
color for=20
  non alpha-transparent output formats, such as JPEG or BMP, in =
hexadecimal=20
  (default: #FFFFFF)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_default_color =3D =
'#FF00FF';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>jpeg_quality</STRONG> sets the compression quality for =
JPEG images=20
  (default: 85)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;jpeg_quality =3D 50;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>jpeg_size</STRONG> if set to a size in bytes, will =
approximate <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$jpeg_quali=
ty">jpeg_quality</A>=20
  so the output image fits within the size (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;jpeg_size =3D 3072;</PRE></LI></UL>The =
following eight settings=20
can be used to invalidate an upload if the file is an image (note that=20
<EM>open_basedir</EM> restrictions prevent the use of these settings)=20
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_max_width</STRONG> if set to a dimension in pixels, =
the=20
  upload will be invalid if the image width is greater (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_max_width =3D 200;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_max_height</STRONG> if set to a dimension in pixels, =
the=20
  upload will be invalid if the image height is greater (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_max_height =3D 100;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_max_pixels</STRONG> if set to a number of pixels, =
the upload=20
  will be invalid if the image number of pixels is greater (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_max_pixels =3D 50000;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_max_ratio</STRONG> if set to a aspect ratio =
(width/height),=20
  the upload will be invalid if the image apect ratio is greater =
(default:=20
  null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_max_ratio =3D 1.5;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_min_width</STRONG> if set to a dimension in pixels, =
the=20
  upload will be invalid if the image width is lower (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_min_width =3D 100;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_min_height</STRONG> if set to a dimension in pixels, =
the=20
  upload will be invalid if the image height is lower (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_min_height =3D 500;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_min_pixels</STRONG> if set to a number of pixels, =
the upload=20
  will be invalid if the image number of pixels is lower (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_min_pixels =3D 20000;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_min_ratio</STRONG> if set to a aspect ratio =
(width/height),=20
  the upload will be invalid if the image apect ratio is lower (default: =

  null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_min_ratio =3D 0.5;</PRE></LI></UL>
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_resize</STRONG> determines is an image will be =
resized=20
  (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_resize =3D =
true;</PRE></LI></UL>The following variables are=20
used only if <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_resi=
ze">image_resize</A>=20
=3D=3D true=20
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_x</STRONG> destination image width (default: =
150)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_x =3D 100;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_y</STRONG> destination image height (default: =
150)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_y =3D 200;</PRE></LI></UL>Use either one =
of the following=20
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio</STRONG> if true, resize image conserving the =
original=20
  sizes ratio, using <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  AND <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  as max sizes if true (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio =
=3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_crop</STRONG> if true, resize image conserving =
the=20
  original sizes ratio, using <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  AND <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  as max sizes, and cropping excedent to fill the space. setting can =
also be a=20
  string, with one or more from 'TBLR', indicating which side of the =
image will=20
  be kept while cropping (default: =
false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_crop =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_fill</STRONG> if true, resize image conserving =
the=20
  original sizes ratio, using <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  AND <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  as max sizes, fitting the image in the space and coloring the =
remaining space.=20
  setting can also be a string, with one or more from 'TBLR', indicating =
which=20
  side of the space the image will be in (default: =
false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_fill =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_no_zoom_in</STRONG> same as <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_rati=
o">image_ratio</A>,=20
  but won't resize if the source image is smaller than <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  x <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_no_zoom_in =3D =
true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_no_zoom_out</STRONG> same as <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_rati=
o">image_ratio</A>,=20
  but won't resize if the source image is bigger than <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  x <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_no_zoom_out =3D =
true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_x</STRONG> if true, resize image, calculating =
<A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  from <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  and conserving the original sizes ratio (default: =
false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_x =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_y</STRONG> if true, resize image, calculating =
<A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  from <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  and conserving the original sizes ratio (default: =
false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_y =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_ratio_pixels</STRONG> if set to a long integer, =
resize=20
  image, calculating <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_y">i=
mage_y</A>=20
  and <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_x">i=
mage_x</A>=20
  to match a the number of pixels (default: =
false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_ratio_pixels =3D =
25000;</PRE></LI></UL>The following image=20
manipulations require GD2+=20
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_brightness</STRONG> if set, corrects the brightness. =
value=20
  between -127 and 127 (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_brightness =3D 40;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_contrast</STRONG> if set, corrects the contrast. =
value=20
  between -127 and 127 (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_contrast =3D 50;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_tint_color</STRONG> if set, will tint the image with =
a=20
  color, value as hexadecimal #FFFFFF (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_tint_color =3D '#FF0000';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_overlay_color</STRONG> if set, will add a colored =
overlay,=20
  value as hexadecimal #FFFFFF (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_overlay_color =3D '#FF0000';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_overlay_percent</STRONG> used when <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$image_over=
lay_color">image_overlay_color</A>=20
  is set, determines the opacity (default: =
50)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_overlay_percent =3D 20;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_negative</STRONG> inverts the colors in the image =
(default:=20
  false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_negative =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_greyscale</STRONG> transforms an image into =
greyscale=20
  (default: false)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_greyscale =3D true;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_threshold</STRONG> applies a threshold filter. value =
between=20
  -127 and 127 (default: null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_threshold =3D =
20;</PRE></LI></UL>
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text</STRONG> creates a text label on the image, =
value is a=20
  string, with eventual replacement tokens (default: =
null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text =3D 'test';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_direction</STRONG> text label direction, either =
'h'=20
  horizontal or 'v' vertical (default: =
'h')<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_direction =3D 'v';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_color</STRONG> text color for the text label, =
in=20
  hexadecimal (default: #FFFFFF)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_color =
=3D '#FF0000';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_percent</STRONG> text opacity on the text =
label,=20
  integer between 0 and 100 (default: =
100)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_percent =3D 50;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_background</STRONG> text label background =
color, in=20
  hexadecimal (default: null)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_background =
=3D '#FFFFFF';</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_background_percent</STRONG> text label =
background=20
  opacity, integer between 0 and 100 (default: =
100)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_background_percent =3D 50;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_font</STRONG> built-in font for the text label, =
from 1=20
  to 5. 1 is the smallest (default: =
5)<BR><PRE>$handle-&gt;image_text_font =3D 4;</PRE>
  <LI><STRONG>image_text_x</STRONG> absolute text label position, in =
pixels from=20
