<P class=3Dshort-description>Crops an image</P>
<P class=3Ddescription>
<P>Values are four dimensions, or two, or one (CSS style) They represent =
the=20
amount cropped top, right, bottom and left. These values can either be =
in an=20
array, or a space separated string. Each value can be in pixels (with or =
without=20
'px'), or percentage (of the source image)</P>
<P>For instance, are valid: <PRE> $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D 20             =
     OR array(20);
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20px'              OR array('20px');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20 40'             OR array('20', 40);
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '-20 25%'           OR array(-20, '25%');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20px 25%'          OR array('20px', '25%');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20% 25%'           OR array('20%', '25%');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20% 25% 10% 30%'   OR array('20%', '25%', =
'10%', '30%');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20px 25px 2px 2px' OR array('20px', '25%px', =
'2px', '2px');
 $foo-&gt;image_crop =3D '20 25% 40px 10%'   OR array(20, '25%', '40px', =
'10%');</PRE>
<P></P>
<P>If a value is negative, the image will be expanded, and the extra =
parts will=20
be filled with black</P>
<P>Default value is null (no cropping)</P>
<P></P>
<UL class=3Dtags>
