<P class=3Dshort-description>Default color for non alpha-transparent =
images</P>
<P class=3Ddescription>
<P>This setting is to be used to define a background color for semi =
transparent=20
areas of an alpha transparent when the output format doesn't support =
alpha=20
transparency This is useful when, from an alpha transparent PNG image, =
or an=20
image with alpha transparent features if you want to output it as a =
transparent=20
GIFs for instance, you can set a blending color for transparent areas If =
you=20
output in JPEG or BMP, this color will be used to fill in the previously =

transparent areas</P>
<P>The default color white</P>
<P></P>
