</DIV><!-- =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D Info from phpDoc block =
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D -->
<P class=3Dshort-description>Actually uploads the file, and act on it =
according to=20
the set processing class variables</P>
<P class=3Ddescription>
<P>This function copies the uploaded file to the given location, =
eventually=20
performing actions on it. Typically, you can call <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
several times for the same file, for instance to create a resized image =
and a=20
thumbnail of the same file. The original uploaded file remains intact in =
its=20
temporary location, so you can use <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
several times. You will be able to delete the uploaded file with <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodclean">c=
lean</A>=20
when you have finished all your <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
calls.</P>
<P>According to the processing class variables set in the calling file, =
the file=20
can be renamed, and if it is an image, can be resized or converted.</P>
<P>When the processing is completed, and the file copied to its new =
location,=20
the processing class variables will be reset to their default value. =
This allows=20
you to set new properties, and perform another <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#methodprocess"=
>process</A>=20
on the same uploaded file</P>
<P>If the function is called with a null or empty argument, then it will =
return=20
the content of the picture</P>
<P>It will set <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$processed"=
>processed</A>=20
(and <A=20
href=3D"http://www.verot.net/res/sources/class.upload.html#var$error">err=
or</A> is=20
an error occurred)</P>
<P></P>
<UL class=3Dtags>
  <LI><SPAN class=3Dfield>return:</SPAN> Optional content of the image=20
  <LI><SPAN class=3Dfield>access:</SPAN> public </LI></UL>
<DIV class=3Dmethod-signature><SPAN class=3Dmethod-result>string</SPAN> =
<SPAN=20
class=3Dmethod-name>process </SPAN>([<SPAN =
class=3Dvar-type>string</SPAN>&nbsp;<SPAN=20
class=3Dvar-name>$server_path</SPAN> =3D <SPAN =
class=3Dvar-default>null</SPAN>])=20
</DIV>
<UL class=3Dparameters>
  <LI><SPAN class=3Dvar-type>string</SPAN> <SPAN=20
  class=3Dvar-name>$server_path</SPAN><SPAN class=3Dvar-description>: =
Optional path=20
  location of the uploaded file, with an ending slash</SPAN>=20
</LI></UL></DIV></DIV></DIV>
